            "title": "Generation 2 Dynatrace Apps for the HoT lab",
            "type": "links"
          },
          {
            "content": "## Description of all document sources\n\nTo enable all important content to be easily accessed, below here is a table with the names of the important content and a short description. Just above this tile, all the content is linked.\n\n| App | Name | Description \n --- | --- | --- \n `Dashboards` | `Advanced Diagnostics` | This is the primary dashboard used in this HoT. Check it out!\n \u0026nbsp; | `Traces on Grail` | Uses various metrics and **traces on Grail** to zoom in to services running the Astroshop, delivering great level of detail across millions of transactions! \n \u0026nbsp; | `Astroshop loadtest overview` | This dashboard focusses on all the loadtests that are executed on the environment. Furthermore additional links are part of the dashboard for easy access.\n `Notebooks` | `DQL for Traces - Dynatrace for Developers` | This is a **awesome** notebook with various hints and tips for using DQL on traces. A great reference that is downloadable and executable on your own tenants when `Traces on Grail` becomes GA. \n `Workflows*` | `astroshop staging quality gate Validation` | This workflow collects various bits of information, creates a ticket, execute a Site Reliability Guardian and finally document the success or failure.\n \u0026nbsp; | `astroshop-cicd-events-smoketest` | This workflow is executed during the build process in order to execute a smoke test to validate the release of the Astroshop deployment.\n `Site Reliability Guardian` | `Astroshop - Staging - Quality gate` | This is the SRG that checks the quality of the deployed ActiveGate by analysing over 20 Service Level Objectives (SLO's)! \n\n* Note: If you do not see any of the workflows in the `Workflows` app, click on your name in the `owner` dropdown and select `Clear selection` so that all created Workflows are shown.\n\n\nUtilise the search function to find the items that are reuired. This also supports searching on a name, returning a specific app and results!",
            "id": "{{ .extractedIDs.id_9dca3fd7_b961_4bc1_8e4f_523a6b6792ac }}",
            "properties": {
              "expanded": true
            },
